---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Timber and Tides Woodcraft"
  description="Learn about the maker behind Timber and Tides Woodcraft, a one-person woodworking shop based in Colorado."
>

  <!-- ── Page Hero ── wood bg ─────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden py-16">
    <div
      class="absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none"
      style="background-image: url('/images/backgrounds/background-1_large.jpg'); background-size: cover; background-position: center;"
    ></div>
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-zinc-900/65 pointer-events-none"></div>

    <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4">
      <span class="inline-block rounded-full bg-black/50 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-secondary ring-1 ring-inset ring-secondary">About</span>
      <h1 class="mt-2 text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">
        Timber and Tides Woodcraft
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-fg leading-relaxed">
        A small one-person shop in Colorado building custom furniture, gifts, and
        functional pieces — one board at a time.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── About the Maker ── dark bg ──────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="py-12">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">The Maker</h2>
      <div class="mt-4 space-y-4 text-muted leading-relaxed">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">From Garage Projects to Fine Furniture</h3>
        <p>
          I grew up working alongside my father in our garage. Most of our projects were construction-related, but every now and then,
          we built cabinets, and those were always my favorite. Before long, I was building small boxes and cabinets of my own to organize
          odds and ends around the house. They were far from perfect, but I was hooked on the process.
          <br><br>During college, I built my first bed frame, a project that marked my transition from simple storage pieces to furniture making. Nearly 13 years later, that bed
          frame is still in use today. Since then, I have developed a dedicated workshop where each new project is an opportunity to push my skills further.
        </p>
        
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Craftsmanship with Purpose</h3>
        <p>
          My background in cabinet making has taught me how to blend function with style. I enjoy tackling projects I have never built
          before, designing custom jigs, and learning new techniques to achieve the best possible results.
          <br><br>From end-grain butcher blocks and custom keepsake pieces to large freestanding furniture, I take pride in creating
          durable, handcrafted works designed to be both beautiful and practical.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Custom Cabinets and Furniture</h3>
        <p>
          I build everything from one-of-a-kind furniture to complete cabinet installations for homes and businesses. Materials are sourced
          locally through various wood suppliers in NoCo, allowing me to use high-quality hardwoods and sheet goods while supporting local businesses.
          <br><br>If you have a project in mind, I would be honored to help bring your ideas to life.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── The Process ── surface bg ───────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="bg-surface py-12">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">The Process</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-muted">
        From concept to craftsmanship to delivery, we make commissioning custom woodworking simple and seamless.
      </p>

      <ol class="mt-6 space-y-6">
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="flex h-8 w-8 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-primary/20 text-sm font-bold text-primary">1</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold">Reach out</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-muted">
              Send an email with a commission request.
              <br><br>Include your name, contact information,project idea, rough dimensions, wood preferences (species of wood, hard or soft wood, etc...), timeline, and your budget.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="flex h-8 w-8 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-primary/20 text-sm font-bold text-primary">2</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold">Design &amp; estimate</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-muted">
              A design deposit will be required for custom projects prior to the start of the design process. I use CAD modeling to give
              you a 3D interactive model that I can modify to meet your vision. The complexity and size of the project will proportionally affect the design fees.
              <br><br>Once we agree on a design, I will lock it in and begin the quote process. Any future changes will have to go through a change order process.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="flex h-8 w-8 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-primary/20 text-sm font-bold text-primary">3</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold">Build</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-muted">
              I construct all projects with strength and quality in mind. I typically use cabinet-grade materials and hardwood for trim. I take great
              pride in a seamless finish, one that will be sure to impress your house guests or business customers.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="flex h-8 w-8 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-primary/20 text-sm font-bold text-primary">4</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold">Delivery</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-muted">
              I can ship anywhere in the lower 48 states. Local delivery is included in every project. “Built-in” projects are available as well.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Materials ── dark bg ─────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="py-12">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">Materials &amp; Finishes</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-muted leading-relaxed">
        It is hard to say what my favorite wood type is, they all have their own beauty...what am I saying, Walnut is the best! Joking aside,
        I love working with whatever I can get my hands on, from softwoods to exotic hardwoods that chew through my blades in a few minutes.
        I love the variation in colors, textures, and smells that every wood species brings!
        <br><br>Wood is sourced from trusted local suppliers whenever possible, with specialty species available through online sourcing when a 
        project calls for it. Standard finishes include Minwax for most projects and food-safe mineral oil for kitchen and dining pieces,
        with custom finish options available upon request.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── CTA ── surface bg ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="bg-surface py-12">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold">Ready to start a project?</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-muted">
        Reach out with your idea and I'll get back to you with questions and a rough estimate.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3">
        <a
          href="/contact/"
          class="inline-flex items-center rounded-xl bg-secondary px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-bg transition hover:brightness-110"
        >
          Request a Commission
        </a>
        <a
          href="/projects/"
          class="inline-flex items-center rounded-xl border border-border bg-surface-2 px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-fg transition hover:bg-surface"
        >
          Browse Projects
        </a>
        <a
          href="https://www.instagram.com/timberandtideswoodcraft/"
          target="_blank"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-xl border border-border bg-surface-2 px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-fg transition hover:bg-surface"
        >
          <svg class="h-4 w-4 shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M12 2.163c3.204 0 3.584.012 4.85.07 3.252.148 4.771 1.691 4.919 4.919.058 1.265.069 1.645.069 4.849 0 3.205-.012 3.584-.069 4.849-.149 3.225-1.664 4.771-4.919 4.919-1.266.058-1.644.07-4.85.07-3.204 0-3.584-.012-4.849-.07-3.26-.149-4.771-1.699-4.919-4.92-.058-1.265-.07-1.644-.07-4.849 0-3.204.013-3.583.07-4.849.149-3.227 1.664-4.771 4.919-4.919 1.266-.057 1.645-.069 4.849-.069zm0-2.163c-3.259 0-3.667.014-4.947.072-4.358.2-6.78 2.618-6.98 6.98-.059 1.281-.073 1.689-.073 4.948 0 3.259.014 3.668.072 4.948.2 4.358 2.618 6.78 6.98 6.98 1.281.058 1.689.072 4.948.072 3.259 0 3.668-.014 4.948-.072 4.354-.2 6.782-2.618 6.979-6.98.059-1.28.073-1.689.073-4.948 0-3.259-.014-3.667-.072-4.947-.196-4.354-2.617-6.78-6.979-6.98-1.281-.059-1.69-.073-4.949-.073zm0 5.838c-3.403 0-6.162 2.759-6.162 6.162s2.759 6.163 6.162 6.163 6.162-2.759 6.162-6.163c0-3.403-2.759-6.162-6.162-6.162zm0 10.162c-2.209 0-4-1.79-4-4 0-2.209 1.791-4 4-4s4 1.791 4 4c0 2.21-1.791 4-4 4zm6.406-11.845c-.796 0-1.441.645-1.441 1.44s.645 1.44 1.441 1.44c.795 0 1.439-.645 1.439-1.44s-.644-1.44-1.439-1.44z"/>
          </svg>
          Follow on Instagram
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
